<emphasis box="[828,1379,646,672]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection</emphasis>
. The comparison was satisfactory, with the exception of the specimen Nº. DGEO-CTG-UFPE-1157, since they presented identical outlines and posterodorsal and ventral overlapping.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,466,1285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,596,754,780]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Occurrence and associated fauna</emphasis>
. It was recorded in the Santo Antonio section, in all depths and associated with all species. It is the only species that occurs associated with the nannofossils 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1280,790,817]" class="Hexanauplia" family="Metidae" genus="Thoracosphaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Harpacticoida" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1056,1241,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Thoracosphaera</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Coccolithophyceae" family="Biscutaceae" genus="Biscutum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Podorhabdales" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" phylum="Haptophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1332,1436,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Biscutum</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(Araripe 
<emphasis box="[292,350,826,852]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">at al.</emphasis>
2022).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,466,1285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,862,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Observations</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[370,576,862,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[440,495,862,888]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
emphasize the sexual dimorphism of this species and describe the male form, however in the present study these forms are described as distinct species, mainly due to the different outlines, since both specimens are smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,466,1285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,510,970,996]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Stratigraphic distribution</emphasis>
. In Africa, it has been commonly recorded in the d’Hama-Koussou Basin, Lower Cretaceous (Aptian) (
<bibRefCitation author="Colin, J. P. &amp; Brunet, M. &amp; Congleton, J. D. &amp; Dejax, J. &amp; Flynn, L. J. &amp; Hell, J. &amp; Jacobs, L." box="[399,604,1006,1032]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="357 - 372" refId="ref13531" refString="Colin, J. P., Brunet, M., Congleton, J. D., Dejax, J., Flynn, L. J., Hell, J. &amp; Jacobs, L. (1992) Ostracodes lacustre des bassins d'age Cretace Inferieur du Nord Cameroun: Hama-Koussou, Koum et Babouri-figuil. Revue de Paleobiologie, 11 (2), 357 - 372." type="journal article" year="1992">
Colin 
<emphasis box="[474,534,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[661,732,1006,1032]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it has been recorded in the Araripe Basin, Crato Formation (Neumann 1999), Aptian; Grajaú Basin, Codó Formation, lower Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos, M. I. F. &amp; Rossetti, D. D. F. &amp; Paz, J. S." box="[980,1196,1042,1068]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="339 - 348" refId="ref16386" refString="Ramos, M. I. F., Rossetti, D. D. F. &amp; Paz, J. S. (2006) Caracterizacao e significado paleoambiental da fauna de ostracodes da Formacao Codo (Neoaptiano), leste da Bacia de Grajau, MA, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Paleontologia, 9, 339 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.4072 / rbp. 2006.3.09" type="journal article" year="2006">
Ramos 
<emphasis box="[1069,1127,1042,1068]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
); Cedro Basin, Crato Formation, upper Aptian (Tomé 2007; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F." box="[581,870,1078,1105]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="56 - 70" refId="ref17032" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. (2010) Ostracodes da Bacia de Cedro, Andar Alagoas, Estado de Pernambuco, NE, Brasil: Implicacoes paleoambientais e bioestratigraficas. Estudos Geologicos, 21, 56 - 70." type="journal article" year="2010">Tome &amp; Lima Filho 2010</bibRefCitation>
); Potiguar Basin, Alagamar Formation, Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Whatley, R. C. &amp; Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P." pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref13960" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Coimbra, J. C., Whatley, R. C., Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P. (2013) Taxonomy of limnic Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Alagamar Formation, middle-upper Aptian, Potiguar Basin, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 108 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[235,293,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). In the 
<collectingRegion box="[455,541,1114,1140]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Sergipe</collectingRegion>
/ 
<collectingRegion box="[549,639,1114,1140]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
Basin, 
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R." box="[726,1074,1114,1140]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref15025" refString="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R. (1971) Ostracoden des &quot; Nordost-Brasilianischen Wealden &quot;. Geologisches Jahrbuch, 115, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1971">Krommelbein &amp; Weber (1971)</bibRefCitation>
observed the occurrence of this species and called it Ostracode 207 (Nº SMF Xe-22592), which is stored in slide PIA-3-AL (obtained from a depth of 
<quantity box="[182,335,1186,1213]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.15" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" unit="m" value="915.0" valueMax="930.0" valueMin="900.0">900 to 930 m</quantity>
) in Frankfurt (
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[501,700,1186,1212]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[574,631,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally found in the Jatobá Basin, Serra Negra Formation, in the strata correlated to the Crato Formation, upper Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[832,1026,1222,1248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="543" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[904,960,1222,1248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="543">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), and this study in the Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, upper Aptian and lower Albian.
</paragraph>
